fetchAdmin

fetchStoreID
isItemBought
fetchStoreBalance

activateEmergencyStop().details: Contract owner activates emergency stop - disables all contract functionality

addAdmin(address).details: Contract owner assigns administrator rights to an ethereum account

addItem(string,uint256,uint256,uint256).details: Store owner adds a new item to a particular store that he/she owns

params._nameOfItem: The display name of the item to be added
params._price: The price per unit of the item to be added
params._quantity: The quantity of the item that is to be added
params._storeID: The unique ID of the store to which the item will be added. The store ID is generated upon store creation

addStoreOwner(address).details: Administrator assigns store owner rights to an ethereum account

buyItem(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: Shopper logs in, browses stores, selects a store, and can purchase an item from the chosen store

params._quantity: The number of units of a chosen item to purchase
params._skuCode: The unique ID of the item to purchase
params._storeID: The unique ID of the store to purchase from (not shown on the UI as by this point, they would already be within the store i.e. store ID is known)

changePrice(uint256,uint256,uint256).details: Store owner changes the price of an already existing item in a particular store that he/she owns

params._newPrice: The new price of the item
params._skuCode: The unique ID belonging to that particular item
params._storeID: The unique ID of the store that the item exists in

createStoreFront(string).details: Store owner creates a new storefront

params._storeName: The display name of the store to create

deActivateEmergencyStop().details: Contract owner deactivates emergency stop - enables all contract functionality

deleteAdmin(address).details: Contract owner revokes administrator rights from an ethereum account

deleteItem(uint256,uint256).details: Store owner deletes an item from a particular store that he/she owns

params._skuCode: The unique ID belonging to that particular item
params._storeID: The unique ID of the store that the item exists in

deleteStoreOwner(address).details: Administrator revokes store owner rights from an ethereum account

fetchAdmin(address).details: Fetches the existence of an admin

params._isAdmin: The address of account to check the admin status of

fetchAdmin(address).return: The status of the account => admin or not admin

fetchStoreBalance(uint256).details: Checks the balance of the store after sales have been made

params._storeID: The store ID for which to check the balance of

fetchStoreBalance(uint256).return: storeBalance The current balance of the store

fetchStoreID(uint256).details: Fetch function used for testing to check that a store was added correctly

params._storeID: The store ID for which to check the store owner and store name of

fetchStoreID(uint256).return: newStoreOwnerAddress The address of account to confirm ownership againststoreNameAdded The name of the store to confirm creation of

fetchStoreOwner(address).details: Fetches the existence of a store owner

params._isStoreOwner: The address of account to check the store owner status of

fetchStoreOwner(address).return: The status of the account => store owner or not store owner

getItemInShop(uint256,uint256).details: Gets the details of each item in a shop to display on the UI

params._sku: The unique ID of each item in a particular store
params._storeID: The unique ID of the store to display the items of

getItemInShop(uint256,uint256).return: itemName The name of the item to displayitemQuantity The number of units of a particular item available in the storeitemPrice The price per unit of item available to purchase

getLatestSKU(uint256).details: Gets the latest sku ID, used as the end parameter of a js loop to display the shop items on the UI

params._storeID: The unique ID of the store to display the items of

getLatestSKU(uint256).return: latestSkuNoInStore The latest item ID added to the store

isItemBought(uint256,uint256).details: Checks that an item quantity has been reduced after a purchase

params._currentSKU: The item ID to retrieve information about
params._currentStoreID: The store ID to retrieve information from

isItemBought(uint256,uint256).return: quantity The balance of items left in the shop

isOwner().return: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

withdrawAllFunds().details: Contract owner withdraws all funds of contract in an emergency situation

withdrawSales(uint256,uint256).details: Store owner withdraws the revenue generated from sales in a particular store

params._storeID: The unique ID of the store to withdraw from
params._withdrawAmount: The amount to withdraw. Can withdraw the full balance or a particular amount, to refund customers for returns for eg

addItem(string,uint256,uint256,uint256).notice: skuCount Generates a unique ID assigned to a newly created item

createStoreFront(string).notice: storeOwner Associates the store and the ownerstoreID Generates a unique ID for the newly added store

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
